  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build composting toilets for 50 families in Malawi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kwathu Foundation is helping subsistance farmers in Mboma village to build composting toilets. At the moment, these farmers do not succeed to harvest enough to prevent hunger, because they can&apos;t afford to by fertilizer. These toilets will not only provide the villagers with free, high-quality organic fertilizer (&apos;humanure&quot;) for their fields, but also improve drinking water quality because these toilets prevent avoid faecal contamination of the groundwater due to lower toilet depth.</narrative>
  </description>
